div1.p: Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.
The People of the United States of America, to No 4704 W. H. Harristhe Sheriff of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of C. H. Hutchinson by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever named said C H Hutchinson shall be called or charged, before the HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Judge of the aforsaid Court at the District Court house of King County on the 12 day of November, 1885 at 2 O'Clock P.M. to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said C H Hutchinson And have then and there this writ.
WITESS THE HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 12th day of November A.D. 1885,
JAMES SEAVEY, Clerk By James P. Ludlow Deputy
In Re Application et C. H. Hutchinson for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
FILED NOV 13 1885 James Seavey, Clerk By James P. Ludluw Deputy Clerk
Rasin & Gilman Jas Hamilton Lewis Peffs Attorneys
